  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for the rapid recovery of families affected by the panning of the earthquake of August 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribution to EA22
Earthquake August 14, 2021. Considerable losses and damage to infrastructure, many homes destroyed. Over 2000 died, over 12,000 were injured. Directly affected around 690,000 people. 

First stage of recovery proposes to: 
1. Support the affected families in the fight against the trauma created by the earthquake.
2. Facilitate the agricultural recovery of 3,000 affected families;
3. Improve the living space of 200 affected families;
4. Support 2000 affected families in the resumption of their economic activities and the care of their children through the development of CASH transfer initiatives;
5. Carry out the organizational diagnosis of Caritas Haiti based on the CI Management Standards.

Direct beneficiaries of recovery phase: 3000 families/ 15,000 people

Geographical reach: Department of Grand-Anse/ Diocese of J&#xE9;r&#xE9;mie; Department of the South / Diocese of Cayes; Department of Nippes / Diocese of Anse-&#xE0;-Veau / Mirago&#xE2;ne.</narrative>
  </description>
